data.name: General.InvalidToolSwitch
data.value: MSB6001: Invalid command line switch for "{0}". {1}
data.comment: {StrBegin="MSB6001: "}UE: This message is shown when a tool-based task (i.e. the task is a wrapper for an .exe) is given a parameter value that converts into an invalid command line switch for the tool. "{0}" is the name of the tool e.g. "csc.exe", and "{1}" is a message explaining the problem. LOCALIZATION: "{1}" is a localized message.
